From: Keel <ci@keel.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH 0001/0006] keel: branding: override product strings to "Keel"

Replaces the product-name string resources Brave inherits from Chromium with
Keel's strings. Only display strings change — channel names, mojo IPC names,
bundle IDs, profile dir, and the User-Agent brand token are deliberately
NOT renamed (see ../branding/README.md for rationale).

Context will drift between Brave releases. If `git apply --check` fails on
this hunk after a rebase, re-locate `IDS_PRODUCT_NAME` (and the matching
`IDS_SHORT_PRODUCT_NAME` and `IDS_PRODUCT_NAME_LONG`) in the current upstream
strings file and update the patch.

---
 brave/app/brave_strings.grdp | 18 ++++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/brave/app/brave_strings.grdp b/brave/app/brave_strings.grdp
--- a/brave/app/brave_strings.grdp
+++ b/brave/app/brave_strings.grdp
@@
   <message name="IDS_PRODUCT_NAME" desc="The Chrome application name">
-    Brave
+    Keel
   </message>
   <message name="IDS_SHORT_PRODUCT_NAME" desc="The Chrome short application name">
-    Brave
+    Keel
   </message>
   <message name="IDS_PRODUCT_NAME_LONG" desc="The Chrome long application name">
-    Brave Browser
+    Keel Browser
   </message>
   <message name="IDS_ABOUT_VERSION_COMPANY_NAME" desc="Company name on the about page">
-    Brave Software Inc.
+    Keel
   </message>
